 is now often taken as an Anglicized form of the Old Welsh name Elisud . It has enjoyed considerable popularity in recent times, having also been taken up as a girl's name."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Dev ."],"variants":[{"name":"Deborah","meanings":["Biblical name (meaning ‘bee’ in Hebrew), borne by the nurse of Rebecca (Genesis 35:8) and by a woman judge and prophet (Judges 4–5) who led the Israelites to victory over the Canaanites. It has always been popular as a Jewish name. It was in use among Christians by the mid 16th century and was taken up by the Puritans in the 17th century, in part because the bee was a symbol of industriousness. Since then it has enjoyed enormous popularity, peaking in the 1960s. Among other famous bearers is the actress  Deborah Kerr  (  1921–2007 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ellis de Bradshaw was born in 1358, in Bolton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Henry Bradshaw, was 23 and his mother, Alice Rivington, was 23. He married Margaret De Worthington in 1380, in Bolton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1403, in his hometown, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1358–1403":"1358–1403","1362–1420":"1362–1420","1360–1403":"1360–1403","1385–1433":"1385–1433","1335–1395":"1335–1395","1335–Female":"1335–Surnud","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1335":"1335","1433":"1433","1355":"1355","1420":"1420","1385":"1385","1395":"1395","1362":"1362","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Bolton, Lancashire, England":"Bolton, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bolton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Bolton, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bradshaw, Bolton, Lancashire, England":"Bradshaw, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Marple, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Marple, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bolton, , Lancashire, England":"B